title: Tracery
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The stonework or ornamental pattern that supports and decorates the glass in a [[Gothic]] window. It divides the window into sections and can form delicate, lace-like designs such as circles, arches, and floral shapes.

''Example:'' The tracery in the [[Rose Window]]s of [[Notre-Dame Cathedral]] in [[Paris]].
